f Jona, to distinguish him from another of the same name (  Simon Zelotes ). ‘When Jesus beheld him, he said, Thou art Simon the son of Jona: thou shalt be called Cephas, which is by interpretation, A stone’ (John 1:42). According to Matthew 16:17–18, Christ says more explicitly, ‘Blessed art thou, Simon Bar-jona … thou art Peter, and upon this rock I will build my church’. The name has been in continuous use since the Middle Ages."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Peter Corbucion I was born about 1115, in Studley, Warwickshire, England, United Kingdom as the son of William Corbucion II. He had at least 2 sons and 1 daughter with Charlecote of Egmanton. He died after 1166, in Chillington Hall, Staffordshire, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"Abt 1115–Aft 1166":"umbes 1115–pärast 1166","1115–1166":"1115–1166","–1170":"–1170","1120–Female":"1120–Surnud","1140–1200":"1140–1200","–1227":"–1227","–Female":"Surnud","1085–Male":"1085–Surnud","1227":"1227","1115":"1115","Aft 1166":"pärast 1166","1200":"1200","1166":"1166","1120":"1120","Abt 1115":"umbes 1115","1140":"1140","1085":"1085","1170":"1170","Chillington Hall, Wolverhampton, Staffordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Chillington Hall, Staffordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Studley, Stratford-on-Avon, Warwickshire, England, United Kingdom":"Studley, Warwickshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1115–Aft 1166":"noin 1115–1166 jälkeen","1115–1166":"1115–1166","–1170":"–1170","1120–Female":"1120–Kuollut","1140–1200":"1140–1200","–1227":"–1227","–Female":"Kuollut","1085–Male":"1085–Kuollut","1227":"1227","1115":"1115","Aft 1166":"1166 jälkeen","1200":"1200","1166":"1166","1120":"1120","Abt 1115":"noin 1115","1140":"1140","1085":"1085","1170":"1170","Chillington Hall, Wolverhampton, Staffordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Chillington Hall, Staffordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Studley, Stratford-on-Avon, Warwickshire, England, United Kingdom":"Studley, Warwickshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskun